5:
Come on, just pick already. We can
do the same boring odd jobs as
usual and get it over with.
8:
I'd love to, but the ones listed today
are all pretty dangerous...
10:
Hmm... How about this one? Think
we can handle it?
15:
Surely you can do better. Pick
something actually fun, like that one.
22:
Don't ask a question you don't want
to know the answer to.
28:
Most normal people would, you
know...
33:
If you're going to be a brat about it, I
may as well kill you now.
37:
Can't... breathe... That's it, I'm adding
"no choking" to the contract!
41:
We move out as soon as you're
ready.
49:
Give it up, Alk. I'd rather face
whatever's out there than her.
55:
Hey, Nimbus. What do you think
goes through the head of a person
like her?
59:
Your mistake there is assuming
she's a "person." She's downright
inhuman.
61:
The two of you couldn't be any more
different. It's no use trying to
understand her.
66:
Despite what people claim, I am
human.
69:
Besides, what qualities define a
person's humanity in the first place?
71:
Do I need to be an idiot, hesitate to
deal the finishing blow and get killed
instead? Is that what it takes?
75:
Hey. You may not like the way he is,
but the rest of us do.
79:
Is that so? You lot make me sick to
my stomach.
82:
I can't wait until the day you finally
lead yourselves to slaughter.
85:
...You think you're better than me,
but we'll see how long you can live
this life of violence and stay that
way.
97:
*wheeze* I figured this was gonna
be tough, considering the reward's
big enough for a whole platoon, but
this is...
100:
These guys don't seem like your
typical adventurers-turned-bandits.
105:
Less talking, more walking. Or do you
want to die?
107:
The rest are this way. Don't fall
behind.
112:
...How much you wanna bet this is a
trap?
115:
For us? Seems like a lot of work for
just us, and I'm not sure a trap would
even work on Shuilong...
120:
I can think of plenty of reasons
someone would want to try though.
123: Some people just can't let things go.
132:
I recall you saying something about
wanting to off my employers before.
134:
So I thought I'd take the opportunity
to introduce you to each other.
137: What... What kind of sick game is this?
139:
What do you WANT FROM ME,
MASTER?!
146:
I gave him some training, since he
seemed like he had a bit of potential
in him.
148:
But it looks like this is as far as he'll
grow. I suppose that's the best that
fodder can do.
151:
What's that supposed to mean?
Look at me! I've grown way stronger
than before!
152:
I offed my old man and all those
other weaklings with the power you
gave me! So why
155: I expect you to listen when I talk.
157:
Now I'll say it one more time. You're.
Fodder. This is your limit.
162:
Fine... If that's the way it's going to
be...
165:
Well, isn't this a fine specimen. How
much did you pay for this one?
167: Is that all you've got to say to me?
170:
I suppose I can be generous, now
that you've piqued my interest.
173:
Dear disciple... I compliment your
fine taste. This monster should
prove to be far more entertaining
than you.
176:
Kill her! Pummel her face into a
bloody pulp! I never want to see that
sick smirk of hers again!
185:
You're going to take pity on him?
You must be asking for an early
grave.
187:
Or do you save weaklings to give
yourself a sense of satisfaction?
199:
But what I care about right now is
that you honor the contract!
204:
You lot are as soft in the head as
you are in the arms.
